The majority of Kenyans are farmers; 

Judith is a 62-year-old mixed farmer based in Runyejes, a remote village in the Kerugoya area of Kenya. Judith has a husband, and at home they have a lovely family. For the last 10 years, Judith has been actively engaged in mixed farming. She sells her farm’s produce at a local market near her home. Her main income sources include milk, eggs, goat farming and vegetables. Her in-depth knowledge of her environment has enabled Judith to get her hands on numerous small business opportunities. 

Judith is seeking a loan to purchase more poultry. She is very passionate about poultry farming. The most enjoyable task to her is raising poultry. Ironically, she doesn't enjoy feeding cows. Having additional poultry on her farm will bring her untold joy. The hens will also increase the farm's egg production and thus increase sales volume. Judith needs to increase her income to take care of her family's expenses.
